  "market_context": "Bearish higher-time-frame bias confirmed on 5-minute chart with SMT between XAGEUR and XAGGBP; equal highs swept, followed by change in state of delivery and V-shaped reversal setup during London/New York overlap session.",
  "key_observation": "Analyst identified a strong bearish hourly bias, sweep of equal highs, SMT confirmation, and a lower-time-frame reversal entry with stop placed above the order block (not the high) to achieve 2R to sell-side liquidity below.",
  "analysis_steps": [
    "Step 1: Identified strong bearish bias on 5-minute chart using 5m-1H model with 'Bias: Bearish' and SMT(Auto) between XAGEUR and XAGGBP.",
    "Step 2: Noted price swept equal highs and formed a change in state of delivery (closure through opposing candles), enabling a reversal setup.",
    "Step 3: Zoomed to 1-minute chart to locate a valid reversal entry zone near an order block at ~41.520–41.580, with stop placed above the order block (41.425–41.650 range) rather than the swing high to preserve 2R risk-reward.",
    "Step 4: Set target at sell-side liquidity below (~41.050–41.115), confirming 2R achievable from entry with stop above order block."
  ],
  "outcome": "Trade executed short with stop at 41.425–41.650, target at 41.050–41.115; achieved 2R profit as price continued lower after reversal.",
  "lessons": "Strong HTF bias allows aggressive LTF reversal entries when paired with SMT and change in state of delivery; stop placement above order block (not swing high) preserves risk-reward while protecting against false breaks.",
